Monbiot clearly knows little about flood defence. Few defences of agricultural land are against floods of more than the ten or twenty year floods.: ie the odds against them failing in any one year are 10to1 or 20 to 1. These probabilities shorten rapidly for periods of 4 or 5 yearsThe other thing is that there is always a bigger flood waiting to happen. Total protection is neither practical nor affordable. The best that can be done is to provide adequate warnings to threatened areas and for people to seek to protect their most valued possessions.I have attended the aftermath of many floods and the skips of possessions are burned in my memory as well as the traumatic effect on those involved.Riverside, Millside, Summerfield are places to avoid when looking for property. When, not if, the nearby river/stream overflows, where silly he water go?



