This is in parts an inaccurate article. Farmers suffer from flooding too. On rivers such as the Kentish Stour obstructions in the river hold the water back and flood areas such as Canterbury as well as the water meadows. Each river has to be treated according to its origins, in some cases dredging and weed clearance is necessary and has been practised for generations to ease the flow through to the estuary.Has George forgotten that once our rivers had watermills and mill pools (10 on the Kentish Stour) controlling flows and necessitating some canalisation above the mill and that they were used for transport for thousands of years?



